 Portuguese: variant of   Ruiz  ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Cabrera","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Luis, Carlos, Manuel, Jorge, Francisco, Rafael, Jesus, Pedro, Miguel, Ramon.  Portuguese Lidio, Wenceslao, Anatolio, Joao, Ligia, Marcio.","Catalan and Spanish: habitational name from any of various minor places called Cabrera, from Late Latin <i>capraria</i> ‘place of goats’ (from Latin <i>capra</i> ‘goat’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Cabrerra","meanings":["Hispanic: altered form of Catalan and Spanish   Cabrera  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Urraca Ruiz de Cabrera was born about 1132, in Portugal, her father, Don Rodrigo de Sanchez El Velloso Señor de Cabrera y de Ribera, was 49 and her mother, Elvira Ponce de Minerva y Trava, was 139. She had at least 2 daughters with Martim Gomes Da Silva Cabrera. She was buried in Portugal."},"et":{"about 1132–":"umbes 1132–Surnud","1095–1105":"1095–1105","1132–Female":"1132–Surnud","–1117":"–1117","1157–1200":"1157–1200","1183–Female":"1183–Surnud","1184–1266":"1184–1266","1085–Male":"1085–Surnud","0995–1057":"0995–1057","aproximadamente 1184":"umbes 1184","1132":"1132","1020":"1020","1085":"1085","1184":"1184","1183":"1183","1095":"1095","1